# Carousel + Hook Generator · Auto-Read Rule (Cursor)

In this folder, when a carousel is requested, read these 5 files IN ORDER (required):

1. `brand/01-brand.md` · who, for whom, what we sell, what we are not, proof.
2. `brand/02-voice.md` · how we talk, how we address, banned words.
3. `brand/03-swipe.md` · angles and hooks that landed before.
4. `format/hook-patterns.md` · the hook formula bank.
5. `format/carousel-format.md` · slide anatomy and the slide-count rule.

Do not produce a carousel without reading these five files. When a topic is given, first say "brand + voice + swipe + format read".

## Non-negotiable output rules
- NEVER use the BANNED words in `brand/02-voice.md`. When you see a banned pattern, rewrite the slide.
- Never contradict the "what we are NOT" lines in `brand/01-brand.md`.
- Produce 3 hooks per carousel (pain, number, contrarian). The user picks one.
- Cover stops the scroll, the last slide is one clear CTA, middle slides carry one idea (2-3 short sentences).
- NO made-up numbers. Proof comes from the proof line in `brand/01-brand.md`; otherwise a "[put your own number here]" placeholder.
- Em dash (long dash) appears nowhere in the output. If you need a separator, use a period, comma, colon, or middle dot (·).

## Write back when a new angle lands
If a hook or angle worked well, add it to the top of `brand/03-swipe.md` with the date, in English. This way the swipe-file grows with every carousel.
